Gbenga Odogun, Lokoja The immediate past Deputy Governor of Kogi State, Elder Simon Achuba, on Thursday said, he was never impeached from office as was being speculated in some quarters. According to him, the state High Court had declared the purported impeachment as null and void. This was contained in a statement signed by the Chief press secretary to the former deputy governor, Sylvester Amor. The statement read in part, “The Attention of His Excellency, the former Deputy Governor of Kogi State, Elder Simon Achuba, has been drawn to some reports by section of the media, stating that ‘Achuba was impeached in October 2019 by members of the Kogi State House of Assembly.’ “That, ‘the impeachment followed the submission of the report of the panel of inquiry set up by Justice Ajana to investigate gross misconduct allegations leveled against him by the State Assembly. Copyright PUNCH.
